## Section 8 — The Beta Period: March–June 2026

### The Mindset

This is not a launch sequence. It is a protected learning period.

March 3 is the start of beta — not a grand opening. The job from March through June 1 is to answer three questions: Do I like doing this? Can I sustain this alongside a job? Do the systems actually work? Athens is the laboratory. The runway is there. No need to be stingy — just be a grownup about spending. The existential weight belongs on the learning, not on the launch day.

Beta means: it's supposed to be rough. The stream overlay doesn't need to be flawless. The first VOD edit doesn't need to be a masterpiece. The Fourthwall store doesn't need every product dialed. Ship it, watch what happens, adjust. The enemy of March 3 isn't a bad launch — it's no launch because something wasn't ready enough.

Courage, not fearlessness. There's no reason to not give this an honest-to-god best shot — building a community, a place, that matters to a small group of people and grows steadily and naturally. That's not reckless. That's the whole point.

### What the Beta Period Is For

- **Finding rhythm.** Editing videos, playing games on stream, writing live, walking around Athens, figuring out the daily and weekly shape of this life — and whether it's sustainable even when a job enters the picture.
- **Building reps.** Every stream is practice. Every VOD edit teaches something. Every piece of content gets slightly better. Perfectionism is the enemy; iteration is the method.
- **Testing systems.** OBS workflow, Discord moderation, Fourthwall integration, lo-fi loop transitions, VOD clipping pipeline — all of it needs to actually run under real conditions, not just look good on paper.
- **Overcoming the blank page.** The hardest part is starting. Once March 3 happens, the inertia flips from "haven't done it yet" to "doing it." Everything gets easier after that.
- **Having fun.** If this isn't enjoyable, it won't last. The beta period is where that gets tested honestly.

